('FISHING_TACKLE', 'equipment', 'Fishing Tackle', '0', NULL, '0.8', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This kit include a collapsible fishing pole, fishhooks, line, lures, and a fishing net. Professional fishing tackle grants a +1 item bonus to checks to fish.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=20'),
('FISHING_TACKLE_PROFESSIONAL', 'equipment', 'Fishing Tackle (Professional)', '3', NULL, '20', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This kit include a collapsible fishing pole, fishhooks, line, lures, and a fishing net. Professional fishing tackle grants a +1 item bonus to checks to fish.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=20'),
('FLINT_AND_STEEL', 'equipment', 'Flint and Steel', '0', NULL, '0.05', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Flint and steel are useful in creating a fire if you have the time to catch a spark, though using them is typically too time-consuming to be practical during an encounter. Even in ideal conditions, using flint and steel to light a flame requires using at least 3 actions, and often significantly longer.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=21'),
('FORMULA_BOOK_BLANK', 'equipment', 'Formula Book (Blank)', '0', NULL, '1', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A formula book holds the formulas necessary to make items other than the common equipment from this chapter; alchemists typically get one for free. Each formula book can hold the formulas for up to 100 different items. Formulas can also appear on parchment sheets, tablets, and almost any other medium; there’s no need for you to copy them into a specific book as long as you can keep them on hand to reference them.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=22'),
('GRAPPLING_HOOK', 'equipment', 'Grappling Hook', '0', NULL, '0.1', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You can throw a grappling hook with a rope tied to it to make a climb easier. To anchor a grappling hook, make an attack roll with the secret trait against a DC depending on the target, typically at least DC 20. On a success, your hook has a firm hold, but on a critical failure, the hook seems like it will hold but actually falls when you’re partway up.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=23'),
('HAMMER', 'equipment', 'Hammer', '0', NULL, '0.1', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=24'),
