<p><b>Trained</b> Will</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Fortitude, Reflex</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> in a number of skills equal to 3 plus your Intelligence modifier. Trained in crafting.</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> simple weapons, alchemical bombs, unarmed attacks</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> light armor, unarmored defense</p>', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Classes.aspx?ID=1'),
('BARBARIAN', 'Barbarian', '<p>Rage consumes you in battle. You delight in wreaking havoc and using powerful weapons to carve through your enemies, relying on astonishing durability without needing complicated techniques or rigid training. Your rages draw upon a vicious instinct, which you might associate with an animal, a spirit, or some part of yourself. To many barbarians, brute force is a hammer and every problem looks like a nail, whereas others try to hold back the storm of emotions inside them and release their rage only when it matters most.
</p>
<p><b>Key Ability</b> Strength</p>
<p><b>Hit Points</b> 12 plus your Constitution modifier</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Perception</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Reflex</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Fortitude, Will</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> in Athletics. Trained in a number of additional skills equal to 3 plus your Intelligence modifier</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> all simple and martial weapons, unarmed attacks</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> light and medium armor, unarmored defense</p>', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Classes.aspx?ID=2'),
('BARD', 'Bard', '<p>You are a master of artistry, a scholar of hidden secrets, and a captivating persuader. Using powerful performances, you influence minds and elevate souls to new levels of heroics. You might use your powers to become a charismatic leader, or perhaps you might instead be a counselor, manipulator, scholar, scoundrel, or virtuoso. While your versatility leads some to consider you a beguiling ne-erdo- well and a jack-of-all-trades, it''s dangerous to dismiss you as a master of none.</p>
<p><b>Key Ability</b> Charisma<br /><b>Hit Points</b> 8 plus your Constitution modifier</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Perception</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Fortitude, Reflex</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Will</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Occultism, Performance and a number of skills equal to 4 plus your Intelligence modifier</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> all simple weapons plus the longsword, rapier, sap, shortsword, shortbow, whip and unarmed attacks</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> light armor and unarmored defense</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> occult spell attacks and occult spell DCs</p>', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Classes.aspx?ID=3'),
('CHAMPION', 'Champion', '<p>You are an emissary of a deity, a devoted servant who has taken up a weighty mantle, and you adhere to a code that holds you apart from those around you. While champions exist for every alignment, as a champion of good, you provide certainty and hope to the innocent. You have powerful defenses that you share freely with your allies and innocent bystanders, as well as holy power you use to end the threat of evil. Your devotion even attracts the attention of holy spirits who aid you on your journey.</p>
<p><b>Key Ability</b> Strength or Dexterity</p>
<p><b>Hit Points</b> 10 plus your Constitution modifier</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Perception</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Reflex</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Fortitude, Will</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Trained in Religion, one skill determined by your choice of deity, a number of additional skills equal to 2 plus your Intelligence modifier.</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> all simple and martial weapons, unarmed attacks</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> all armor and unarmored defense</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> in divine spell attacks and divine spell DCs</p>', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Classes.aspx?ID=4'),
('CLERIC', 'Cleric', '<p>Deities work their will upon the world in infinite ways, and you serve as one of their most stalwart mortal servants. Blessed with divine magic, you live the ideals of your faith, adorn yourself with the symbols of your church, and train diligently to wield your deity''s favored weapon. Your spells might protect and heal your allies, or they might punish foes and enemies of your faith, as your deity wills. Yours is a life of devotion, spreading the teachings of your faith through both word and deed.</p>
<p><b>Key Ability</b> Wisdom<br /><b>Hit Points</b> 8 plus your Constitution modifier</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Perception</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Fortitude and Reflex</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Will</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Religion, one skill determined by your choice of deity,  a number of additional skills equal to 2 plus your Intelligence modifier</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> all simple weapons and the favored weapon of your deity. If your deity''s favored weapon is uncommon, you also gain access to that weapon.</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Untrained in all armor, though your doctrine might alter this. Trained in unarmored defense</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> divine spell attacks and divine spell DCs</p>', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Classes.aspx?ID=5'),
('DRUID', 'Druid', '<p>The power of nature is impossible to resist. It can bring ruin to the stoutest fortress in minutes, reducing even the mightiest works to rubble, burning them to ash, burying them beneath an avalanche of snow, or drowning them beneath the waves. It can provide endless bounty and breathtaking splendor to those who respect it - and an agonizing death to those who take it too lightly. You are one of those who hear nature''s call. You stand in awe of the majesty of its power and give yourself over to its service.</p>
<p><b>Key Ability</b> Wisdom</p>
<p><b>Hit Points</b> 8 plus your Constitution modifier</p>
<p><b>Perception</b> Trained</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Fortitude and Reflex</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Will</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Trained in Nature. Trained in one skill determined by your choice of order. Trained in a number of additional skills equal to 2 plus your Intelligence modifier</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> all simple weapons and unarmed attacks</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> all light and medium armor, unarmored defense</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> primal spell attacks and primal spell DCs</p>', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Classes.aspx?ID=6'),
('FIGHTER', 'Fighter', '<p>Fighting for honor, greed, loyalty, or simply the thrill of battle, you are an undisputed master of weaponry and combat techniques. You combine your actions through clever combinations of opening moves, finishing strikes, and counterattacks whenever your foes are unwise enough to drop their guard. Whether you are a knight, mercenary, sharpshooter, or blade master, you have honed your martial skills into an art form and perform devastating critical attacks on your enemies.</p>
<p><b>Key Ability</b> Strength or Dexterity</p>
<p><b>Hit Points</b> 10 plus your Constitution modifier</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Perception</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Will</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Fortitude, Reflex</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> a number of skills equal to 3 plus your Intelligence modifier. Trained in your choice of Acrobatics or Athletics</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> all simple and martial weapons, unarmed attacks <b>Trained</b> in advanced weapons</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> all armor and unarmored defense</p>', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Classes.aspx?ID=7'),
('MONK', 'Monk', '<p>The strength of your fist flows from your mind and spirit. You seek perfection - honing your body into a flawless instrument and your mind into an orderly bastion of wisdom. You''re a fierce combatant renowned for martial arts skills and combat stances that grant you unique fighting moves. While the challenge of mastering many fighting styles drives you to great heights, you also enjoy meditating on philosophical questions and discovering new ways to obtain peace and enlightenment.</p>
<p><b>Key Ability</b> Dexterity or Strength<br /><b>Hit Points</b> 10 plus your Constitution modifier</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Perception</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Fortitude<br /><b>Expert</b> Reflex<br /><b>Expert</b> Will</p>
<p><b>Trained</b>Trained in a number of additional skills equal to 4 plus your Intelligence modifier</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> all unarmed attacks and simple weapons</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> in unarmored defense</p>', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Classes.aspx?ID=8'),
('RANGER', 'Ranger', '<p>Some rangers believe civilization wears down the soul, but still needs to be protected from wild creatures. Others say nature needs to be protected from the greedy, who wish to tame its beauty and plunder its treasures. You could champion either goal, or both. You might be a scout, tracker, or hunter of fugitives or beasts, haunting the edge of civilization or exploring the wilds. You know how to live off the land and are skilled at spotting and taking down both opportune prey and hated enemies.</p>
<p><b>Key Ability</b> Dexterity or Strength<br /><b>Hit Points</b> 10 plus your Constitution modifier</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Perception</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Fortitude, Reflex.</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Will</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> in Nature and Survival and a number of skills equal to 4 plus your Intelligence modifier.</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> all simple and martial weapons, unarmed attacks</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> light armor and medium armor, unarmored defense</p>', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Classes.aspx?ID=9'),
('ROGUE', 'Rogue', '<p>You are skilled and opportunistic . Using your sharp wits and quick reactions, you take advantage of your opponents'' missteps and strike where it hurts most. You play a dangerous game, seeking thrills and testing your skills, and likely don''t care much for any laws that happen to get in your way. While the path of every rogue is unique and riddled with danger, the one thing you all share in common is the breadth and depth of your skills.</p>
<p><b>Key Ability</b> Dexterity or other</p>
<p><b>Hit Points</b> 8 plus your Constitution modifier</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Perception</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Fortitude</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Reflex, Will</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> a number of skills equal to 7 plus your Intelligence modifier. Trained in Stealth</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> all simple weapons, plus the rapier, sap, shortbow, shortsword and unarmed attacks</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> light armor and unarmored defense</p>', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Classes.aspx?ID=10'),
('SORCERER', 'Sorcerer', '<p>You didn''t choose to become a spellcaster- you were born one. There''s magic in your blood, whether a divinity touched one of your ancestors, a forebear communed with a primal creature, or a powerful occult ritual influenced your line. Self-reflection and study allow you to refine your inherent magical skills and unlock new, more powerful abilities. The power in your blood carries a risk, however, and you constantly face the choice of whether you''ll rise to become a master spellcaster or fall into destruction.</p>
<p><b>Key Ability</b> Charisma</p>
<p><b>Hit Points</b> 6 + your Constitution modifier</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Perception</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Fortitude, Reflex</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Will</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Trained in one or more skills determined by your bloodline. Trained in a number of additional skills equal to 2 plus your Intelligence modifier</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> simple weapons and unarmed attacks</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> unarmored defense</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> arcane, divine, occult, or primal spell attacks and spell DCs,  as indicated by your bloodline</p>', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Classes.aspx?ID=11'),
('WIZARD', 'Wizard', '<p>You are an eternal student of the arcane secrets of the universe, using your mastery of magic to cast powerful and devastating spells. You treat magic like a science, cross-referencing the latest texts on practical spellcraft with ancient esoteric tomes to discover and understand how magic works. Yet magical theory is vast, and there''s no way you can study it all. You either specialize in one of the eight schools of magic, gaining deeper understanding of the nuances of those spells above all others, or favor a broader approach that emphasizes the way all magic comes together at the expense of depth.</p>
<p><b>Key Ability</b> Intelligence<br /><b>Hit Points</b> 6 plus your Constitution modifier</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Perception</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Fortitude, Reflex</p>
<p><b>Expert</b> Will</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> Trained in Arcana. Trained in a number of additional skills equal to 2 plus your Intelligence modifier</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> the club, dagger, heavy crossbow, light crossbow, staff and unarmed attacks</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> unarmored defense</p>
<p><b>Trained</b> arcane spell attacks and spell DCs</p>', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Classes.aspx?ID=12');


CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS "background" (
    "id" VARCHAR,
    "name" VARCHAR,
    "boost_ref_1" VARCHAR,
    "boost_ref_2" VARCHAR,
    "free_feat_id" VARCHAR,
    "free_feat_category" VARCHAR,
    "free_feat_detail" VARCHAR,
    "lore" VARCHAR,
    "skill" VARCHAR,
    "description" VARCHAR,
    "src" VARCHAR,
    "url" VARCHAR,
    FOREIGN KEY ("boost_ref_1") REFERENCES "ability_score"("id"),
    FOREIGN KEY ("boost_ref_2") REFERENCES "ability_score"("id"),
    FOREIGN KEY ("free_feat_id","free_feat_category") REFERENCES "feat"("id","category"),
    FOREIGN KEY ("src") REFERENCES "rules_source"("id"),
    PRIMARY KEY ("id")
);
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Occultism skill and the Spirit Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Recognize Spell skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/adherent/'),
('ARCHAEOLOGIST', 'Archaeologist', 'CON', 'INT', 'ODDITY_IDENTIFICATION', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Ancient Regional', 'Occultism', '<p>Whether you''re a fascinated outsider or a local proud of your nation''s storied past, you''re a devoted student of history. You might be a traveling professor, a member of a society like the Adventurer''s Guild, or even a simple tomb robber cashing in on the glories of the past.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Intelligence, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Occultism skill and the Ancient Regional Lore skill. You gain the Oddity Identification skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/archaeologist/'),
('ARTIFACT_SEEKER', 'Artifact Seeker', 'DEX', 'INT', 'SPECIALTY_CRAFTING', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Regional', 'Crafting', '<p>You''ve dedicated your life to unraveling the secrets of ancient empires, either through meticulous research or by traveling into dangerous and distant ruins to track down long-lost artifacts.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Intelligence, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Crafting skill and a Regional Lore skill. You gain the Specialty Crafting skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/artifact-seeker/'),
('ASPIRING_FREE_CAPTAIN', 'Aspiring Free Captain', 'WIS', 'CHA', 'GROUP_COERCION', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Sailing', 'Intimidation', '<p>You have learned everything you need to know about sailing and bossing people around. Now you just need a crew and a ship.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Wisdom or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Intimidation skill and the Sailing Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Group Coercion skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/aspiring-free-captain/'),
('ASPIRING_RIVER_MONARCH', 'Aspiring River Monarch', 'WIS', 'CHA', 'COURTLY_GRACES', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Politics', 'Society', '<p>New realms rise constantly, and you intend to lead one of them. Making your reign last, however, will require both strength and grace.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Wisdom or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Society skill and the Politics Lore skill. You gain the Courtly Graces skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/aspiring-river-monarch/'),
('BLACK_MARKET_SMUGGLER', 'Black Market Smuggler', 'WIS', 'CHA', 'EXPERIENCED_SMUGGLER', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Underworld', 'Stealth', '<p>You know how to work the less-than-legal side of the region''s markets and know how to slip contraband past the authorities.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Wisdom or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Stealth skill and the Underworld Lore skill. You gain the Experienced Smuggler skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/black-market-smuggler/'),
('BRIGHT_LION', 'Bright Lion', 'STR', 'CHA', 'LIE_TO_ME', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Regional', 'Deception', '<p>You seek to overthrow tyranny.</p>
<p>You''re experienced operating undercover and have had to be cautious of what you say and who you trust, lest you fall afoul of the god-king''s terrible punishments.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Strength or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Deception skill and a Regional Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Lie to Me skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/bright-lion/'),
('CHARMER', 'Charmer', 'INT', 'CHA', 'CHARMING_LIAR', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Underworld', 'Deception', '<p>You grew up steeped in the cultural legacy of pirates and smugglers, and you rely on your cleverness and charm as you make your way throughout the world.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Intelligence or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Deception skill and the Underworld Lore skill. You gain the Charming Liar skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/charmer/'),
('CHILD_OF_SQUALOR', 'Child of Squalor', 'DEX', 'INT', 'STEADY_BALANCE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Regional', 'Acrobatics', '<p>You''re at home in tightly packed urban environments.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Intelligence, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Acrobatics skill and a Regional Lore skill. You gain the Steady Balance skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/child-of-the-puddles/'),
('CHILD_OF_THE_CITY', 'Child of the City', 'STR', 'CHA', 'GROUP_IMPRESSION', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Regional', 'Diplomacy', '<p>You are proud of your country and do not consider yourself a rebel.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Strength or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Diplomacy skill and a Regional Lore skill. You gain the Group Impression skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/child-of-the-city/'),
('CRUSADER', 'Crusader', 'CON', 'WIS', 'STUDENT_OF_THE_CANON', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Undead', 'Religion', '<p>You grew up considering the existence of an undead nation an atrocity and trained to one day take part in destroying it and putting its vile inhabitants to their final rest. Key to your preparations is a thorough study of undead-related deities and their philosophies.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Religion skill and the Undead Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Student of the Canon skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/crusader/'),
('CURSED_FAMILY', 'Cursed Family', 'INT', 'CHA', 'ODDITY_IDENTIFICATION', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Curse', 'Occultism', '<p>Rumors abound that your family is cursed. While that would explain several unfortunate events in your family history, you may or may not believe it. Regardless, odd coincidences plague your lineage, and perhaps even appear in your own life, and you have become used to spotting strangeness around you.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Intelligence or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Occultism skill and the Curse Lore skill. You gain the Oddity Identification skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/cursed-family/'),
('DESERT_TRACKER', 'Desert Tracker', 'CON', 'WIS', 'EXPERIENCED_TRACKER', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Desert', 'Survival', '<p>You''re at home blazing trails in the burning sands, and you made a living guiding or following creatures in the desert. You might be a native nomad, an experienced desert guide, a naturalist, a bandit driven into the dunes by the law-or all of the above.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Survival skill and the Desert Lore skill. You gain the Experienced Tracker skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/desert-tracker/'),
('EMISSARY_POLITICAL', 'Emissary (Political)', 'CHA', 'INT', 'MULTILINGUAL', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Politics', 'Society', '<p>You were trained to be an ambassador, and you have now been sent out into the wider world to build alliances between neighboring kingdoms.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Charisma or Intelligence, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Society skill and the Politics Lore skill. You gain the Multilingual skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/emissary-2/'),
('EXPATRIATE', 'Expatriate', 'INT', 'CHA', 'SKILL_TRAINING', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Dragon', 'Society', '<p>You have been exiled, perhaps of your own accord or perhaps because you didn''t measure up. However, you take with you some of the benefits of the excellent education afforded to its citizenry.</p>
<p>Choose two ability boosts.</p>
<p>One must be to Intelligence or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Society skill and the Dragon Lore skill. You gain the Skill Training skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/expatriate/'),
('FAITHFUL', 'Faithful', 'STR', 'CHA', 'GROUP_COERCION', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Regional', 'Intimidation', '<p>You serve a living god, and this gives your actions a divine mandate not to be trifled with.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Strength or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Intimidation skill and a Regional Lore skill. You gain the Group Coercion skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/faithful/'),
('FOLLOWER', 'Follower', 'CON', 'INT', 'BARGAIN_HUNTER', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Regional', 'Diplomacy', '<p>You seek to build your wealth in this life so that you might meet the next world on your own terms.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Intelligence, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Diplomacy skill and a Regional Lore skill. You gain the Bargain Hunter skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/follower/'),
('FREED_SLAVE', 'Freed Slave', 'CON', 'INT', 'STREETWISE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Absalom', 'Society', '<p>As a recently freed slave you belong to a new, closeknit social class at the heart of the city''s most important trades.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Intelligence, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Society skill and the Absalom Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Streetwise skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/freed-slave/'),
('GOBLINBLOOD_ORPHAN', 'Goblinblood Orphan', 'DEX', 'CON', 'ASSURANCE', 'GENERAL', 'Survival', 'Goblin', 'Survival', '<p>Your family, whether goblin, hobgoblin, or human, died in the goblin wars. Though you were marked by these losses, you managed to survive through your own resilience and resourcefulness.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Constitution, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Survival skill and the Goblin Lore skill. You gain the Assurance skill feat with Survival.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/goblinblood-orphan/'),
('GRAND_COUNCIL_BUREAUCRAT', 'Grand Council Bureaucrat', 'CHA', 'INT', 'GROUP_IMPRESSION', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Government', 'Society', '<p>You spent years working as a clerk. Your service taught you a thing or two about rousing speeches and manipulating the city''s bureaucracy.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Charisma or Intelligence, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Society skill and the Government Lore skill. You gain the Group Impression skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/grand-council-bureaucrat/'),
('GUERRILLA', 'Guerrilla', 'DEX', 'WIS', 'TERRAIN_STALKER', 'GENERAL', 'Underbrush', 'Forest', 'Survival', '<p>Woodcraft comes naturally to you, and you have learned how to use the forest to your tactical advantage against superior forces.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Survival skill and the Forest Lore skill. You gain the Terrain Stalker (underbrush) skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/guerrilla/'),
('HOPEFUL', 'Hopeful', 'CON', 'INT', 'ADDITIONAL_LORE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Adventurer''s Society', 'Society', '<p>You''ve long wanted to join an adventurer''s guild.</p>
<p>You have taken up the dangerous life of an adventurer.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Intelligence, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Society skill and the Adventurer''s Society Lore skill. You gain the Additional Lore skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/hopeful/'),
('INLANDER', 'Inlander', 'CON', 'WIS', 'SURVEY_WILDLIFE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Terrain', 'Survival', '<p>You grew up in an untamed region and you know how to survive in the wild.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Survival skill and a Lore skill related to the terrain type associated with your home region (such as Hills Lore or Mountains Lore). You gain the Survey Wildlife skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/inlander/'),
('LOYALIST', 'Loyalist', 'INT', 'CHA', 'STUDENT_OF_THE_CANON', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Hell', 'Religion', '<p>You consider the current queen to be the rightful ruler of your homeland, and you are willing to act against her enemies.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Intelligence or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Religion skill and the Hell Lore skill</p>
<p>You gain the Student of the Canon skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/loyalist/'),
('LUMBERJACK', 'Lumberjack', 'STR', 'DEX', 'ASSURANCE', 'GENERAL', 'Athletics', 'Forest', 'Athletics', '<p>You have suffered as a worker, laboring under harsh conditions in dangerous wooded regions.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Strength or Dexterity, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Athletics skill and the Forest Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Assurance skill feat with Athletics.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/lumberjack/'),
('MAMMOTH_SPEAKER', 'Mammoth Speaker', 'CON', 'WIS', 'TRAIN_ANIMAL', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Animal', 'Nature', '<p>You have learned the secrets of taming the mighty mammoths and other megafauna of the far north. Perhaps these talents are a part of your people''s traditional customs, or perhaps you sought out these massive animals of your own accord.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Nature skill and the Animal Lore skill. You gain the Train Animal skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/mammoth-speaker/'),
('MANTIS_SCION', 'Mantis Scion', 'DEX', 'WIS', 'ASSURANCE', 'GENERAL', 'Stealth', 'Assassin', 'Stealth', '<p>At least one of your parents is a member of the notorious Crimson assassins, merciless killers for hire who rarely fail to claim their marks. Whether on purpose or by simple exposure, you were trained from a young age in the art of stalking and killing people.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Stealth skill and the Assassin Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Assurance skill feat with Stealth.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/mantis-scion/'),
('MENAGERIE_DUNG_SWEEPER', 'Menagerie Dung Sweeper', 'CON', 'WIS', 'TRAIN_ANIMAL', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Animal', 'Nature', '<p>Whether you washed warrior beasts below arena floor or tended to the mutated animals of a sideshow, you are experienced with all manner of weird wildlife.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Nature skill and the Animal Lore skill. You gain the Train Animal skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/menagerie-dung-sweeper/'),
('MERCENARY', 'Mercenary', 'STR', 'CON', 'EXPERIENCED_PROFESSIONAL', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Mercenary', 'Athletics', '<p>Whether you sought citizenship or simply needed a steady paycheck, you spent some of your time as a paid mercenary. Alternatively, you might have worked at sea, protecting military and trading ships against pirates.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Strength or Constitution, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Athletics skill and the Mercenary Lore skill. You gain the Experienced Professional skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/mercenary/'),
('MYSTIC', 'Mystic', 'INT', 'WIS', 'ARCANE_SENSE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'A plane', 'Arcana', '<p>Your initiations grant you a preternatural comprehension of the arcane underpinnings of existence.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Intelligence or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Arcana skill and a Lore skill related to one plane of your choice (other than the Material Plane). You gain the Arcane Sense skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/mystic/'),
('NAME_BEARER', 'Name-Bearer', 'STR', 'WIS', 'COMBAT_CLIMBER', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Quah', 'Athletics', '<p>You have gone through a coming of age ceremony, gaining the traditional tattoo and earning your adult name.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Strength or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Athletics skill and the Quah Lore skill. You gain the Combat Climber skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/name-bearer/'),
('ONYX_TRADER', 'Onyx Trader', 'DEX', 'CHA', 'MULTILINGUAL', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Mercantile', 'Society', '<p>You have traveled and traded goods across a wide variety of lands. You''ve learned to step lively in foreign markets of all types.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Society skill and the Mercantile Lore skill. You gain the Multilingual skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/onyx-trader/'),
('OOZE_TENDER', 'Ooze-Tender', 'CON', 'INT', 'DUBIOUS_KNOWLEDGE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Ooze', 'Crafting', '<p>Your apprenticeship instilled in you a deep reservoir of mostly reliable esoteric knowledge, not to mention a deep resentment born of countless hours spent mucking ooze pens and feeding helpless creatures to ravenous, belching jellies and gelatinous puddings.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Intelligence, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Crafting skill and the Ooze Lore skill. You gain the Dubious Knowledge skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/ooze-tender/'),
('PARTISAN', 'Partisan', 'CON', 'CHA', 'GROUP_IMPRESSION', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Politics', 'Diplomacy', '<p>You''re accustomed to arguing from a position of underappreciated worth.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Diplomacy skill and the Politics Lore skill. You gain the Group Impression skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/partisan/'),
('PEARL_DIVER', 'Pearl Diver', 'CON', 'DEX', 'UNDERWATER_MARAUDER', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Ocean', 'Athletics', '<p>You spent a portion of your youth diving and gathering precious pearls.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Dexterity, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Athletics skill and the Ocean Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Underwater Marauder skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/pearl-diver/'),
('PERFECTION_SEEKER', 'Perfection Seeker', 'DEX', 'WIS', 'CAT_FALL', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Warfare', 'Acrobatics', '<p>You aspire to perfect your body and mind, honing your acrobatic skills and mental faculties in preparation for a lifetime pushing the edge of what most consider possible.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Acrobatics skill as well as the Warfare Lore skill. You gain the Cat Fall skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/perfection-seeker/'),
('PRESS_GANGED', 'Press-Ganged', 'STR', 'WIS', 'EXPERIENCED_PROFESSIONAL', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Sailing', 'Society', '<p>You were forced into service as a sailor against your will.</p>
<p>Perhaps you were punished for a crime, were drafted into military service, are repaying a debt, or simply were abducted.</p>
<p>Though you were initially trained as a simple deckhand, you may have subsequently studied a trade under one of the vessel''s specialists.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Strength or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Society skill and the Sailing Lore skill. You gain the Experienced Professional skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/press-ganged/'),
('PRODIGY', 'Prodigy', 'DEX', 'INT', 'SPECIALTY_CRAFTING', 'GENERAL', 'Alchemy', 'Alchemical', 'Crafting', '<p>Even in a city renowned for its alchemy, you were able to rise above the competition.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Intelligence, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Crafting skill and the Alchemical Lore skill. You gain the Specialty Crafting skill feat with alchemy.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/prodigy/'),
('PURVEYOR_OF_THE_BIZARRE', 'Purveyor of the Bizarre', 'INT', 'WIS', 'QUICK_IDENTIFICATION', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Mercantile', 'Arcana', '<p>You''ve spent enough time buying and selling ancient or unusual items to give you an instinctive ability to quickly sort valuable trinkets from worthless baubles.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Intelligence or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Arcana skill and the Mercantile Lore skill. You gain the Quick Identification skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/purveyor-of-the-bizarre/'),
('QUICK', 'Quick', 'CHA', 'CON', 'CHARMING_LIAR', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Undead', 'Deception', '<p>Staying alive among scheming, ravenous undead required a deep knowledge of their motivations, capabilities, and weaknesses. More often than not, it also required the ability to weave alibis and life-preserving half-truths capable of swaying a stilled heart.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Charisma or Constitution, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Deception skill and the Undead Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Charming Liar skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/quick/'),
('RAIDER', 'Raider', 'STR', 'CHA', 'INTIMIDATING_GLARE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Sailing', 'Intimidation', '<p>You are feared for the merciless and devastating raids your people once conducted. You have been trained to strike terror into the hearts of those who face you.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Strength or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Intimidation skill and the Sailing Lore skill. You gain the Intimidating Glare skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/raider/'),
('RANCHER', 'Rancher', 'STR', 'DEX', 'TRAIN_ANIMAL', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Animal', 'Nature', '<p>You grew up breeding and training horses.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Strength or Dexterity, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Nature skill and the Animal Lore skill. You gain the Train Animal skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/rancher/'),
('REBEL', 'Rebel', 'DEX', 'CHA', 'STREETWISE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Regional', 'Society', '<p>You may have helped liberate a nation, or you might be involved in another rebellion.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Society skill and a Regional Lore skill. You gain the Streetwise skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/rebel/'),
('RECLAIMER', 'Reclaimer', 'CON', 'WIS', 'BATTLE_MEDICINE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Abyssal', 'Medicine', '<p>You seek to liberate a land from the demons who have defiled it.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Wisdom, and one is a free boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Medicine skill and the Abyssal Lore skill. You gain the Battle Medicine skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/reclaimer/'),
('REFORMER', 'Reformer', 'DEX', 'CHA', 'HOBNOBBER', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Politics', 'Diplomacy', '<p>You know that the only way your homeland can remain free from outside conquerors is by forging a strong and unified government. As such, you seek to bind your fellow citizens together through careful diplomacy and force of personality-or, if necessary, subterfuge and intrigue.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Diplomacy skill and the Politics Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Hobnobber skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/reformer/'),
('REFUGEE', 'Refugee', 'CON', 'INT', 'TRICK_MAGIC_ITEM', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Wilderness', 'Arcana', '<p>Exposure to the corrupting influence of the Mana Wastes'' strange energies has warped your inner essence, resulting in unpredictable interactions with magic items and more than a little know-how about surviving under bizarre and adverse natural conditions.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Intelligence, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Arcana skill and the Wilderness Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Trick Magic Item skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Backgrounds.aspx?ID=90'),
('RESTORER', 'Restorer', 'WIS', 'CHA', 'GROUP_IMPRESSION', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Abyss', 'Diplomacy', '<p>Though many worship demons, you seek to pave a different path for yourself and your kindred, while also attempting to change other''s treatment of your culture.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Wisdom or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Diplomacy skill and the Abyss Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Group Impression skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/restorer/'),
('SENGHOR_SAILOR', 'Sailor', 'INT', 'WIS', 'QUICK_REPAIR', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Sailing', 'Crafting', '<p>As an experienced sailor, you know that the only thing saving you from disaster on the high seas is a properly maintained ship. You know boat-building inside and out and you can quickly cobble together a solution in the event that something breaks.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Intelligence or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Crafting skill and the Sailing Lore skill. You gain the Quick Repair skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Backgrounds.aspx?ID=99'),
('SCAVENGER', 'Scavenger', 'CON', 'WIS', 'FORAGER', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Swamp', 'Survival', '<p>You''ve managed to eke out an existence in the storm-wracked Sodden Lands and have become an expert at scavenging food and tools.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Survival skill and the Swamp Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Forager skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/scavenger/'),
('SCHEMER', 'Schemer', 'CHA', 'CON', 'HOBNOBBER', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Politics', 'Diplomacy', '<p>Whether willing or unwilling, you have been involved in the many cutthroat political intrigues. You might have been born into it as a member of the aristocracy, or you might have taken an active role in recent events.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Charisma or Constitution, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Diplomacy skill and the Politics Lore skill. You gain the Hobnobber skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/schemer/'),
('SCHOLAR_OF_THE_ANCIENTS', 'Scholar of the Ancients', 'INT', 'CHA', 'QUICK_IDENTIFICATION', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Regional', 'Arcana', '<p>You''re fascinated by lost empires and have dedicated yourself to seeking out and studying every broken artifact or scrap of knowledge that remains, whether as an academic pursuit or simply for the joy of treasure hunting.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Intelligence or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Arcana skill and a Regional Lore skills. You gain the Quick Identification skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/scholar-of-the-ancients/'),
('SCION', 'Scion', 'INT', 'WIS', 'STUDENT_OF_THE_CANON', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Undead', 'Religion', '<p>Your family has long been associated with an enigmatic death cult. Whether or not you have followed in their footsteps, you know many of the philosophy''s secrets.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Intelligence or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Religion skill and the Undead Lore skill. You gain the Student of the Canon skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/scion/'),
('SECULAR_MEDIC', 'Secular Medic', 'WIS', 'DEX', 'BATTLE_MEDICINE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Anatomy', 'Medicine', '<p>You''ve thrown yourself into the study of medicine, so you can save lives without saving souls.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Wisdom or Dexterity, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Medicine skill and the Anatomy Lore skill. You gain the Battle Medicine skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/secular-medic/'),
('SHADOW_HAUNTED', 'Shadow Haunted', 'INT', 'WIS', 'QUICK_COERCION', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Shadow Plane', 'Intimidation', '<p>A dark entity has a claim on your soul due to an ancient pact.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Intelligence or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Intimidation skill and the Shadow Plane Lore skill. You gain the Quick Coercion skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/shadow-haunted/'),
('SLAYER', 'Slayer', 'STR', 'CHA', 'INTIMIDATING_GLARE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Orc', 'Intimidation', '<p>You are a fearsome warrior, and your clan counts on you for support, counsel, and defense.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Strength or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Intimidation skill and the Orc Lore skill. You gain the Intimidating Glare skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/slayer/'),
('SMUGGLER', 'Smuggler', 'DEX', 'CHA', 'EXPERIENCED_SMUGGLER', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Underworld', 'Stealth', '<p>You know how to smuggle people in and out of countries.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Stealth skill and the Underworld Lore skill. You gain the Experienced Smuggler skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/smuggler/'),
('STORM_SURVIVOR', 'Storm Survivor', 'STR', 'WIS', 'FORAGER', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Weather', 'Survival', '<p>Through luck or through skill, you managed to survive a catastrophic maritime disaster, such as a shipwreck or being thrown overboard. You have a keen sense for weather or situations that are similar to the one you escaped.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Strength or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Survival skill and the Weather Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Forager skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/storm-survivor/'),
('SURVIVOR', 'Survivor', 'CHA', 'WIS', 'CHARMING_LIAR', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Revolution', 'Deception', '<p>You were scheduled for execution, but through skill-or sheer luck-you managed to talk your way out of it.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Charisma or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Deception skill and the Revolution Lore skill. You gain the Charming Liar skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/survivor-3/'),
('ALKENSTAR_TINKER', 'Tinker', 'DEX', 'INT', 'ALCHEMICAL_CRAFTING', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Engineering', 'Crafting', '<p>Your dedication to scientific inquiry provides great insight into mechanical and chemical innovation.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Intelligence, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Crafting skill and the Engineering Lore skill. You gain the Alchemical Crafting skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/tinker-2/'),
('TRADE_CONSORTIUM_UNDERLING', 'Trade Consortium Underling', 'INT', 'WIS', 'EXPERIENCED_PROFESSIONAL', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Business', 'Society', '<p>Your experience as a ledger-keeper for a trade guild has made you a canny investor and shrewd entrepreneur.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Intelligence or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Society skill and the Business Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Experienced Professional skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/trade-consortium-underling/'),
('TRAVELER', 'Traveler', 'CON', 'INT', 'DUBIOUS_KNOWLEDGE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Regional', 'Arcana', '<p>You know many things that have been long forgotten... along with many things that are no longer correct.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Intelligence, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Arcana skill and a Regional Lore skill. You gain the Dubious Knowledge skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/traveler/'),
('UNDERSEA_ENTHUSIAST', 'Undersea Enthusiast', 'STR', 'CON', 'UNDERWATER_MARAUDER', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Ocean', 'Athletics', '<p>You love diving and exploring the world beneath the waves, and long periods of swimming have trained you to move easily through the water. You''re also fascinated by undersea creatures and cultures-and may even have a trace of one of them in your own lineage.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Strength or Constitution, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Athletics skill and the Ocean Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Underwater Marauder skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/undersea-enthusiast/'),
('UNIFIER', 'Unifier', 'STR', 'CHA', 'QUICK_COERCION', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Politics', 'Intimidation', '<p>You believe the various city-states should be united into one nation under the rule of your home city, and you''re willing to do whatever it takes to make it happen.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Strength or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Intimidation skill and the Politics Lore skill. You gain the Quick Coercion skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/unifier/'),
('WANDERER', 'Wanderer', 'DEX', 'CHA', 'FASCINATING_PERFORMANCE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Circus', 'Performance', '<p>You have heard endless tales of your people''s history and lore, and have learned many songs and stories from the disparate people you have met.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Performance skill and the Circus Lore skill. You gain the Fascinating Performance skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/wanderer/'),
('WAVETOUCHED', 'Wavetouched', 'STR', 'WIS', 'UNDERWATER_MARAUDER', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Ocean', 'Athletics', '<p>The sea''s salt flows through your veins. You''ve taken to sailing and swimming gracefully and with ease, earning you the honorific "wavetouched". </p>
<p>Choose two ability boosts. One must be to Strength or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Athletics skill and the Ocean Lore skill.</p>
<p>You gain the Underwater Marauder skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/wavetouched/'),
('WILDBORNE', 'Wildborne', 'DEX', 'WIS', 'NATURAL_MEDICINE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Forest', 'Nature', '<p>You might have been born and raised among the druids, or you may have spent time among them as an adult and come to know their ways.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Nature skill as well as the Forest Lore skill. You gain the Natural Medicine skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/wildborne/'),
('WINTER''S_CHILD', 'Winter''s Child', 'CON', 'CHA', 'ARCANE_SENSE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Weather', 'Arcana', '<p>The blood of Baba Yaga''s legacy runs in your veins, and you are at one with the mysteries and dangers of the frozen land.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Constitution or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Arcana skill and the Weather Lore skill. You gain the Arcane Sense skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/winters-child/'),
('WITCH_WARY', 'Witch Wary', 'DEX', 'INT', 'ODDITY_IDENTIFICATION', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Curse', 'Occultism', '<p>You have little love or trust for spellcraft and those who practice it, and have developed a paranoid knack for recognizing such tricks. You are constantly on guard for the magic of witches and have been trained to spot the signs of those with minds affected by magic.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Dexterity or Intelligence, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Occultism skill and the Curse Lore skill. You gain the Oddity Identification skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/witch-wary/'),
('WONDER_TASTER', 'Wonder Taster', 'INT', 'CON', 'ALCHEMICAL_CRAFTING', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Alchemical', 'Crafting', '<p>You''ve tasted knowledge beyond comprehension. You are driven to recapture that astounding experience.</p>
<p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Intelligence or Constitution, and one is a free ability boost.</p>
<p>You''re trained in the Crafting skill and the Alchemical Lore skill. You gain the Alchemical Crafting skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/wonder-taster/'),
('ACADEMIC', 'Academic', 'INT', 'WIS', 'SKILL_TRAINING', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Academia', 'Crafting', '<p>You were educated at a famed academy and received quality instruction in advanced concepts of mathematics, science, and engineering.</p><p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Intelligence or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.</p><p>You''re trained in the Crafting skill and the Academia Lore skill. You gain the Skill Training skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/academic-2/'),
('ACADEMIC_NATURE', 'Academic (Nature)', 'INT', 'CHA', 'RECOGNIZE_SPELL', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Academia', 'Nature', '<p>You studied magic at a prestigious academy, learning magical traditions and earning a pedigree respected by magical scholars almost everywhere.</p><p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Intelligence or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p><p>You''re trained in your choice of either the Arcana or Nature skill, as well as the Academia Lore skill. You gain the Recognize Spell skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/academic/'),
('ACADEMIC_ARCANA', 'Academic (Arcana)', 'INT', 'CHA', 'RECOGNIZE_SPELL', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Academia', 'Arcana', '<p>You studied magic at a prestigious academy, learning magical traditions and earning a pedigree respected by magical scholars almost everywhere.</p><p><b>Choose two ability boosts</b>. One must be to Intelligence or Charisma, and one is a free ability boost.</p><p>You''re trained in your choice of either the Arcana or Nature skill, as well as the Academia Lore skill. You gain the Recognize Spell skill feat.</p>', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'http://pf2.d20pfsrd.com/background/academic/'),
('LAST_SURVIVOR', 'Last Survivor', 'CON', 'WIS', 'BATTLE_MEDICINE', 'GENERAL', NULL, 'Undead', 'Medicine', 'Choose two ability boosts. One must be to <b>Constitution</b> or <b>Wisdom</b>, and one is a free ability boost.<br /><br />You''re trained in the Medicine skill and the Undead Lore skill. You gain the Battle Medicine skill feat.', 'LOST_OMENS_WORLD_GUIDE', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Backgrounds.aspx?ID=68');


